                </ul>
                <p>A <span class="font-weight-700">169 mm ground clearance</span> is excellent for an electric scooter, allowing the Orbiter to safely navigate the notorious speed breakers and potholes that characterize many urban and semi-urban roads without scraping the undercarriage. This practical dimension ensures stress-free navigation over unpredictable terrain.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">The Tech Advantage: Smart Connectivity and Features</h3>
                <p>In today's connected world, a premium scooter is to be a smart device on wheels, and the TVS Orbiter delivers with a rich suite of technology features.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">The Connected Mobile App and Cluster</h5>
                <p>The core of the Orbiter’s smart features is its <span class="font-weight-700">Connected Mobile App</span>, which integrates seamlessly with the scooter’s dashboard via <span class="font-weight-700">Bluetooth connection</span>. The rider interface is a clear <span class="font-weight-700">5.5-inch Coloured LCD screen</span>, a sophisticated size and type that provides all necessary information at a glance.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/oct/tvs orbiter scooter/App Connectivity img.webp" alt="App Connectivity img" title="App Connectivity img" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>Key connected features include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">TBT (Turn-By-Turn) Navigation:</span> This is vital for city navigation, displaying directions directly on the cluster, eliminating the need to constantly look down at a phone.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">OTA (Over-The-Air) Updates:</span> This future-proofs the scooter, allowing TVS to push software updates, feature enhancements, and bug fixes remotely, ensuring the vehicle’s technology remains current throughout its lifespan.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>These technological elements turn the Orbiter into a truly personalized vehicle, enhancing safety and convenience by keeping the rider informed and focused on the road.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Unmatched Storage Utility</h5>
                <p>The TVS Orbiter sets a high bar for utility with a massive <span class="font-weight-700">34 L of boot space</span>. This is marketed as <span class="font-weight-700">Twin Helmet Space</span>, a feature that drastically enhances the scooter's daily practicality. Most scooters can only accommodate one full-face helmet; the Orbiter’s ability to store two or equivalent luggage space solves a major pain point for riders who frequently travel with a pillion or require ample storage for work, shopping, or deliveries. <span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub</span> believes that this 34L boot space is a critical differentiator for customers prioritizing maximum utility and convenience in their electric scooter choice.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Braking, Wheels, and Safety System</h5>
                <p>Safety is non-negotiable, and the Orbiter is equipped with a reliable setup.</p>
